Arsenal could potentially play Manchester City in the fourth round of the FA Cup. Mikel Arteta’s side play League One side Oxford United on Monday evening, Manchester City booked their place in the fourth round with a comfortable 4-0 victory over Chelsea at the Etihad Stadium on Sunday. Elsewhere in the fourth round, Manchester United host Reading at Old Trafford, while Liverpool face a trip to Brighton if they beat Wolves in their third-round replay. Tottenham take on Preston North End, while non-league Wrexham host Sheffield United at the Racecourse Ground. The fourth round is scheduled to be played across January 27 to January 30. For more stories like this, check our sport page. Follow Metro Sport for the latest news on 
Facebook, Twitter and Instagram. 